        "text": "The Brandenburg Division belonged to a category unlike any other formation in this archive: it was raised not by the regular army or the Waffen-SS but by the Abwehr, German military intelligence, specifically to conduct covert and deception operations rather than conventional combat. Its soldiers trained in foreign languages, foreign uniforms, and the customs of the countries they would operate in, blurring the line between soldier and intelligence operative."
