        "text": "The Walloon Legion belonged to the family of foreign volunteer formations the Waffen-SS recruited from across occupied and allied Europe — units raised not from German conscripts but from ideologically sympathetic or anti-communist volunteers in France, the Netherlands, Scandinavia, the Balkans, and, here, French-speaking Belgium. It was created in August 1941 in the weeks following the invasion of the Soviet Union, when Léon Degrelle's Rexist movement offered a contingent of Walloon volunteers to fight alongside Germany against Bolshevism."
